    <directions>
        <!-- STEPS -->
        <step>Saut√® the onion in butter. Add rice and stir for a few mins</step>
        <step>Sweat with white wine</step>
        <step>Add a couple of ladles of stock, salt, and stir in vigorously</step>
        <step>Add the endive.</step>
        <step>Carry on adding the stock one ladlef at the time, stirring in strongly, and letting it stand until absorbed</step>
        <step>After 30 mins or so the risotto will be ready. It should be coocked through but still firm.</step>
        <step>Turn off the heat, add the smoked cheese and parmesan, stirring vigorously, and let it stand covered for a few minutes.</step>
        <step>Serve with the hazelnuts sprinkled over the top</step>
    </directions>
